China and Russia argue that the UN Security Council should reward Pyongyang for the measures taken.
U.S. Secretary of State Mike Pompeo told the U.N. Security Council on Thursday that “the implementation of Security Council sanctions must necessarily continue until complete, final and verified nuclear disarmament takes place.”
The Security Council has unanimously strengthened sanctions against North Korea since 2006 in a bid to halt funding for Pyongyang’s nuclear and ballistic missile programs.
