They want to gain popularity on my back, but that's part of the job.
I’m a happy man and everything is fine,” the footballer smiled.
Ronaldo’s lawyers are preparing to sue Der Spiegel for what they call “unacceptable publication of privacy suspicions,” according to Reuters.
Lawyer Christian Schertz said the footballer will seek compensation for "moral damages in an amount commensurate with the gravity of the violation, which is probably one of the most serious violations of personal rights in recent years."
The incident allegedly took place in June 2009 in an apartment at the Palms Hotel and Casino in Las Vegas.
After meeting at a nightclub, Ronaldo and Mayorga went to the player’s room, where it is alleged that he raped her anal, according to documents filed in the Clark County District Court in Nevada.
Mayorga said Ronaldo fell to his knees after the incident and told her he was a "good boy" of "99 percent", but in the case he simply succumbed to the "one percent".
